          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "High purity N2 gas (99.9999%) in stainless steel cells",
                "windowed with 50-100 micrometer thick Al foils from",
                "Goodfellow. Target pressure was 1-2 bar."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV",
                "EXTB",
                "STTA",
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "",
                "The primary deuteron energies were 13.5 and 10 MeV.",
                "Beam current 50-100 nA was measured in Faraday cup.",
                "natTi(d,x)48V monitor reaction was also used.",
                "Aluminium foils were used as energy degrader",
                " 50-300 micrometer.",
                "The decay was followed to be able to separate the 3",
                "produced positron emitter isotopes, then decay curve",
                "analysis was performed.",
                "Nuclear data were taken from E.Brwne and R.B.Firestone",
                "Table of Radioactive Isotopes Ed.V.S.Shirley,",
                "Wiley 1986.",
                "The mean energy in the foils and cells were calculated",
                "using C.F. Williamson, J.P. Boujot, J.Picard:",
                "Tables of Rangeand Stopping Power of Chemical Elements",
                "for Charged Particles of Energy 0.05 to 500 MeV.",
                "Rapport Cea-R-3042, Saclay, France, 1966."
              ]
            }
          ],
